HEADWORD: Antarctic
<hw>Ant*arc"tic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>antartik</ets>, OF. <ets>antartique</ets>, F.
<ets>antarctique</ets>, L. <ets>antarcticus</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/;
<grk>'anti`</grk> + <grk>'a`rktos</grk> bear. See
<er>Arctic</er>.]</ety> <def>Opposite to the northern or arctic pole;
relating to the southern pole or to the region near it, and applied
especially to a circle, distant from the pole 23⟦deg⟧ 28⟦min⟧. Thus we
say the <xex>antarctic</xex> pole, circle, ocean, region, current,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

